docs.abstract: The new CBS News chief, Susan Zirinsky, announces a fresh start after workplace misconduct scandals involving Charlie Rose, Jeff Fager and Leslie Moonves.

docs.lead_paragraph: Like any family reunion, the gathering inside CBS News on Monday had joys and tensions alike.

headline.main: CBS Names Norah O’Donnell as Lead Anchor, Signaling a New Era

docs.abstract: Ms. Nevins left HBO after nearly 40 years in 2017. She will start a nonfiction film and specials division for MTV, which has been trying to turn itself around.
docs.snippet: Ms. Nevins left HBO after nearly 40 years in 2017. She will start a nonfiction film and specials division for MTV, which has been trying to turn itself around.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Sheila Nevins, the grande dame of documentary film, who left HBO in 2017 after nearly 40 years, has joined MTV to start a nonfiction film and specials division.

headline.main: Sheila Nevins, Documentary Film Queen, Joins MTV
headline.print_headline: Documentary Queen To Open MTV Team

docs.abstract: The woman leading Australia’s inquiry into workplace sexual harassment is trying to overcome nondisclosure agreements that prevent victims from talking.
docs.snippet: The woman leading Australia’s inquiry into workplace sexual harassment is trying to overcome nondisclosure agreements that prevent victims from talking.
docs.lead_paragraph: SYDNEY, Australia — Kate Jenkins was hopeful when she opened Australia’s first national inquiry into workplace sexual harassment. As a longtime employment lawyer, she had negotiated settlements for companies dealing with harassment claims. Now, as the country’s sex discrimination commissioner, she knew chief executives who were emphatic about gender equity, in pay and promotion.

headline.main: Employers Who Talk Up Gender Equity, but Silence Harassment Victims
headline.print_headline: Making Vow Of Equality, But Silencing The Abused

docs.abstract: Alan Bergman was promoted to co-chairman of Walt Disney Studios, and Alan Horn, chairman, extended his contract. In a separate move, the producer Amy Pascal will leave Sony for Universal.
docs.snippet: Alan Bergman was promoted to co-chairman of Walt Disney Studios, and Alan Horn, chairman, extended his contract. In a separate move, the producer Amy Pascal will leave Sony for Universal.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Two of the film industry’s fiercest competitors, Walt Disney Studios and Universal Pictures, each made moves to strengthen themselves on Wednesday.

headline.main: Disney and Universal Shore Up Their Benches

docs.abstract: Lawyers for HBO said the Jackson estate’s argument that “Leaving Neverland” violated a nondisparagement clause was a “poorly disguised and legally barred posthumous defamation claim.”
docs.snippet: Lawyers for HBO said the Jackson estate’s argument that “Leaving Neverland” violated a nondisparagement clause was a “poorly disguised and legally barred posthumous defamation claim.”
docs.lead_paragraph: Two months after HBO broadcast “Leaving Neverland,” which detailed allegations of child molestation against Michael Jackson, a legal dispute between the cable channel and the Jackson estate has intensified, with HBO firing back over claims that it violated an old contract by showing the documentary.

headline.main: HBO Pushes Back in Michael Jackson Legal Fight
headline.print_headline: HBO Argues With Estate Of Jackson Over Film

docs.abstract: Confusion inside Boeing about features related to a new software system underline the flawed design and rollout of the company’s troubled new jet.
docs.snippet: Confusion inside Boeing about features related to a new software system underline the flawed design and rollout of the company’s troubled new jet.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Boeing began delivering its 737 Max to customers in 2017, the company believed that a key cockpit warning light was a standard feature in all of the new jets.

headline.main: Boeing Believed a 737 Max Warning Light Was Standard. It Wasn’t.
headline.print_headline: Confusion Leads to Mix-up On 737 Max Warning Light

docs.abstract: The president’s threat was aimed at forcing Beijing to agree to a final trade deal on America’s terms this week in Washington.
docs.snippet: The president’s threat was aimed at forcing Beijing to agree to a final trade deal on America’s terms this week in Washington.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump, emboldened by a strong American economy and wary of criticism that an evolving trade deal with China would not adequately benefit the United States, threatened on Sunday to impose more punishing tariffs on Chinese goods in an attempt to force additional concessions in a final agreement.

headline.main: Trump Threatens China With More Tariffs Ahead of Final Trade Talks
headline.print_headline: As Talks Loom, President Aims At Tariffs Anew

byline.original: By Ana Swanson and Keith Bradsher

docs.abstract: The newspaper chain’s incumbent board members won re-election on Thursday, staving off an attempt by MediaNews Group to gain influence.
docs.snippet: The newspaper chain’s incumbent board members won re-election on Thursday, staving off an attempt by MediaNews Group to gain influence.
docs.lead_paragraph: Gannett, the owner of USA Today and dozens of other newspapers nationwide, on Thursday won the latest round in its battle with a hedge fund-backed media company intent on buying the chain.

headline.main: Gannett Counters the Latest Move by Its Hedge Fund-Backed Rival
headline.print_headline: Gannett Parries Takeover Bid by Hedge Fund

docs.abstract: Global investors grew calmer after Beijing’s retaliatory tariffs shook markets, but sharp rhetoric suggested the uncertainty was far from over.

docs.lead_paragraph: Stocks jumped on Tuesday, rebounding from their biggest loss in more than four months and giving investors a reprieve from the waves of selling that have characterized trading so far in May.

docs.abstract: After Disney acquired most of Rupert Murdoch’s entertainment empire, the fourth network goes back to its campy roots.
docs.snippet: After Disney acquired most of Rupert Murdoch’s entertainment empire, the fourth network goes back to its campy roots.
docs.lead_paragraph: The TV industry is unveiling its coming season to advertisers in Manhattan this week at a series of events known as the upfronts. Three New York Times media reporters — John Koblin, Michael M. Grynbaum and Edmund Lee — assess the Fox presentation at the Beacon Theater on Monday. Fox was the second of the four major broadcast networks to hype its fall wares.

headline.main: A Slimmed-Down Fox Network Touts a ‘Beverly Hills 90210’ Reboot
headline.print_headline: A Scrappier Fox Network Channels Its Early Days

byline.original: By John Koblin, Michael M. Grynbaum and Edmund Lee
